    "problemStatement": "<p dir=\"ltr\"><b><strong>Antonyms</strong></b><span> are words or phrases that have the opposite meaning of another word or phrase in the same language.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Using antonyms in writing helps to create contrast, highlight differences, and bring clarity to your message. They are especially useful when you want to emphasize opposing ideas or show change. Just like synonyms, antonyms can add variety to your writing and prevent it from becoming repetitive or one-dimensional.</span></p><h3 id=\"examples-of-antonyms-includes-opposite-words-such-as\" style=\"text-align:left\"><span>Examples of antonyms include opposite words such as:</span></h3><table><thead><tr><th><span>Word</span></th><th><span>Opposite</span></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><span>Abundant</span></td><td><span>Scarce</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Accept</span></td><td><span>Reject</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Acceptable</span></td><td><span>Unacceptable</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Accurate</span></td><td><span>Inaccurate</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Active</span></td><td><span>Passive</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Add</span></td><td><span>Subtract</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Adequate</span></td><td><span>Inadequate</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Admit</span></td><td><span>Deny</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Advance</span></td><td><span>Retreat</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Advantage</span></td><td><span>Disadvantage</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Ancient</span></td><td><span>Modern</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Artificial</span></td><td><span>Natural</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Arrive</span></td><td><span>Depart</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Benevolent</span></td><td><span>Malevolent</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Big</span></td><td><span>Small</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Black</span></td><td><span>White</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Bold</span></td><td><span>Timid</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Borrow</span></td><td><span>Lend</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Brave</span></td><td><span>Cowardly</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Brief</span></td><td><span>Lengthy</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Buy</span></td><td><span>Sell</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Calm</span></td><td><span>Agitated</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Careful</span></td><td><span>Careless</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Cheap</span></td><td><span>Expensive</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Complex</span></td><td><span>Simple</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Compliment</span></td><td><span>Insult</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Conceal</span></td><td><span>Reveal</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Create</span></td><td><span>Destroy</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Cruel</span></td><td><span>Kind</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Dangerous</span></td><td><span>Safe</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Day</span></td><td><span>Night</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Defend</span></td><td><span>Attack</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Deficit</span></td><td><span>Surplus</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Deliberate</span></td><td><span>Accidental</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Dense</span></td><td><span>Sparse</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Diminish</span></td><td><span>Increase</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Distant</span></td><td><span>Near</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Efficient</span></td><td><span>Inefficient</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Elaborate</span></td><td><span>Simple</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Embrace</span></td><td><span>Reject</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Empty</span></td><td><span>Full</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Expand</span></td><td><span>Contract</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Fast</span></td><td><span>Slow</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Flexible</span></td><td><span>Rigid</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Friendly</span></td><td><span>Hostile</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Full</span></td><td><span>Empty</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Generous</span></td><td><span>Stingy</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Genuine</span></td><td><span>Fake</span></td></tr><tr><td><span>Gentle</span></td>